From 19b19f39fd6a907078f999648faa584cde331c74 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sean Smith <DefendTheDisabled@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 20:20:50 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 15/16] btrfs: add BTRFS_SEND_A_PTIME attribute number
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds BTRFS_SEND_A_PTIME = 36 to the send-stream attribute enum
and bumps __BTRFS_SEND_A_MAX from 35 to 36. BTRFS_SEND_A_MAX_V3
remains 35 — ptime is a v2+-gated extension that sits outside
the historical v3 attribute bucket (see the inline comment
added here), matching how OTIME was retrofitted into the v1
numbering space but only emitted from v2 onward.

This does NOT introduce a new send_stream protocol version.
The attribute is gated at emission by the existing
sctx->proto >= 2 check (the same gate as BTRFS_SEND_A_OTIME).
A v1 stream omits ptime entirely. Patched receivers parse
ptime when present; unpatched receivers reject the unknown
attribute number (userspace TLV parser hard-fails on
attr > __BTRFS_SEND_A_MAX). This is the documented
compatibility boundary for local btrbk deployments where
both sender and receiver are patched.

Ref: Decision #78 (Btrfs send/receive ptime patch)
Files: fs/btrfs/send.h (BTRFS_SEND_A_PTIME, __BTRFS_SEND_A_MAX)
---
 fs/btrfs/send.h | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/fs/btrfs/send.h b/fs/btrfs/send.h
index 652bb28f63d4..b00033ea0fd6 100644
--- a/fs/btrfs/send.h
+++ b/fs/btrfs/send.h
@@ -179,7 +179,14 @@ enum {
 	BTRFS_SEND_A_VERITY_SIG_DATA	= 35,
 	BTRFS_SEND_A_MAX_V3		= 35,
 
-	__BTRFS_SEND_A_MAX		= 35,
+	/*
+	 * Provenance time extension. Added after v3; gated at
+	 * emission by sctx->proto >= 2 (matches OTIME pattern).
+	 * Not part of the v1/v2/v3 version buckets.
+	 */
+	BTRFS_SEND_A_PTIME		= 36,
+
+	__BTRFS_SEND_A_MAX		= 36,
 };
 
 long btrfs_ioctl_send(struct btrfs_root *send_root, const struct btrfs_ioctl_send_args *arg);
